<exercise>
  <statement>
    <p> [Problem A] Let <m>T\colon \mathbb R^n\to \mathbb R^n</m> denote a linear operator and let <m>B</m> be an ortonormal basis of  <m>\mathbb R^n</m>. Let <m>A'</m> denote the matrix of  <m>T</m> with respect to the basis <m>B</m> (considered on both the domain and codomain). 
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                 Prove that <m>T</m> is orthogonal if and only if  <m>A'</m> is an orthogonal matrix.     
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Assume <m>n=3</m>. Prove that <m>T</m> is a rotation if and only if <m>A'\in SO_3</m>. 
               </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>  
  <hint>
    <p>
     For (a), use Propositions 5.1.14 and 4.2.13. For (b), you may use Euler's theorem as well. 
    </p>
  </hint>
</exercise>



